					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737#post-4650401</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737/scp-5707#post-4650401</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2020 20:28:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>redredred</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5379342</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There's no reason this anomaly is Uncle Sam narrative-wise besides just being a hook which fails to follow through. Besides that, the meat of this article is the characterization of the anomaly<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-965975-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup>, which fails to capture me due to a lack of tension and conflict. Sure, he disagrees with the ASCI over whether he should be contained, but it's never developed beyond &quot;I'm a patriot and all, but goddamn guys I'm not going to keep turning children into Spam.&quot; The Foundation is secretly using his ability to essentially feed human meat to D-Class, but he never gets a chance to respond to it and grow as a character. This article is thwacked off at the trunk, so the anomaly never gets the chance to grow into a truly fleshed-out character.</p> <p>This is a -1 from me.</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-965975-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Along with some minor gore in the testing log, which I have to admit that I enjoyed.</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737#post-4650044</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737/scp-5707#post-4650044</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2020 14:08:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tyumen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2951719</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Oh, I'm historically illiterate. I had no idea that Sam Wilson ever existed!</p> <p>Also, I didn't &quot;somewhat&quot; enjoy it - I enjoyed it wholeheartedly, and this story being based on a real person just furthered my enjoyment. Fine work, DrAkimoto.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737#post-4650024</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737/scp-5707#post-4650024</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2020 14:01:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrAkimoto</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5255688</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>To be honest it had to be the real uncle Sam. Uncle Sam really was a meatpacker named <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samuel_Wilson">Samuel Wilson</a> who was in the army and a contracted meat supplier during the War of 1812. Anyway, I'm glad you somewhat enjoyed it!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737#post-4650015</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13320737/scp-5707#post-4650015</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2020 13:56:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tyumen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2951719</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p><em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zi3_eXup12s">&quot;Don't get caught with your fingers in my meat!</a></em><br /> <em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zi3_eXup12s">Grab a plate and boy, you're surely gonna eat!</a></em><br /> <em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zi3_eXup12s">If ever you're in doubt about how this feast began,</a></em><br /> <em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zi3_eXup12s">I make &quot;beef&quot; out of human flesh, I'm Karcist Uncle Sam!&quot;</a></em></p> </blockquote> <p>This was quite an interesting SCP, and I honestly have (mostly positive) mixed feelings about it. On one hand, the man being Uncle Sam himself seems a bit&#8230;on-the-nose. On the other hand, the characterization is excellent, and the article itself is very well-written. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
